100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On January 14, 1926, the League of Nations held discussions in Geneva regarding the ongoing tensions in the Balkans, reflecting ongoing concerns about stability in post-war Europe. In the United States, the Supreme Court ruled on a key case involving the rights of labor unions, potentially impacting workers' rights nationwide. Meanwhile, the exploration of the Arctic continued to capture public interest, as scientists and adventurers sought to unlock its mysteries.
